<font color="#808080">(GAGS)</font>

08:52.063 --> 08:55.267
Oh, I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

08:55.268 --> 08:57.302
Oh fuck. I'm so sorry.

08:57.303 --> 08:59.604
- Oh shit.
- <font color="#808080">(MUTTERS)</font>

08:59.605 --> 09:00.906
Hey, I'll get an ambulance.

09:00.907 --> 09:03.608
Oh fuck. Oh fuck.

09:03.609 --> 09:05.844
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTS)</font>
Take this.

09:05.845 --> 09:07.579
- <font color="#808080">(GROANING)</font>
- It's okay. I'm gonna get help.

09:07.580 --> 09:09.281
I'm gonna get an ambulance,
all right? Hold in there.

09:09.282 --> 09:10.648
<i><font color="#808080">(METAL CLICKS)</font>
</i>

09:12.851 --> 09:14.785
<font color="#808080">(MOANING)</font>

09:17.989 --> 09:20.324
Okay. Okay.

09:21.626 --> 09:23.795
Hey. Two minutes. I promise.

09:23.796 --> 09:26.164
- Don't leave me.
- Just gonna call an ambulance.

09:26.165 --> 09:28.098
I'll be back in two minutes.

09:34.940 --> 09:37.107
<font color="#808080">(GRUNTS, PANTING)</font>

09:38.310 --> 09:40.345
<font color="#808080">(CLICKS)</font>

09:40.346 --> 09:42.581
<font color="#804040">WOMAN</font>: <i>911, what's
your emergency?</i>

09:42.582 --> 09:45.350
I need an ambulance. A
guy's been hit by a car.

09:45.351 --> 09:47.953
- <i>What's the location, Sir?</i>
- Uh, Keeler.

09:47.954 --> 09:50.689
- Keeler and 26th.
- <i>What's your name, Sir?</i>

09:50.690 --> 09:53.158
Please just hurry. Hurry,
he's hurt real bad.

09:53.159 --> 09:55.059
- <i>Sir.</i>
- <font color="#808080">(CLATTERS)</font>

10:07.238 --> 10:09.908
- <font color="#808080">(GROANS)</font>
- The ambulance is coming.

10:09.909 --> 10:12.711
- Don't leave me.
- I have to go. I can't stay.

10:12.712 --> 10:14.245
I can't stay. You'll be fine.

10:14.246 --> 10:16.247
I promise. I promise. I'm sorry.

10:16.248 --> 10:17.349
- Please. No.
- I have to go.

10:17.350 --> 10:19.883
- Please.
- Please. Please.

10:20.852 --> 10:23.253
Fuck. Fuck.

10:25.724 --> 10:27.158
An ambulance is coming, okay?

10:27.159 --> 10:29.727
- <i><font color="#808080">(TRAIN CLATTERING)</font></i>
- Okay?

10:36.868 --> 10:39.770
<font color="#808080">(TIRES SCREECH)</font>

10:41.740 --> 10:43.907
<i><font color="#808080">(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)</font>
</i>

11:03.762 --> 11:05.929
<font color="#808080">(CLICKS, SQUEAKING)</font>

11:16.808 --> 11:19.144
- <i><font color="#808080">(GEAR SHIFT CLICKS)</font></i>
- <i><font color="#808080">(ENGINE STOPS)</font></i>

11:19.145 --> 11:21.311
<i><font color="#808080">(GARAGE DOOR CLOSING)</font>
</i>

11:59.718 --> 12:01.885
<font color="#808080">(SHOWER RUNNING)</font>

12:17.836 --> 12:20.003
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font>

12:28.813 --> 12:31.014
<font color="#808080">(SIGHING)</font>

12:42.060 --> 12:44.328
Don't leave me, please.

12:51.870 --> 12:54.806
- There's daddy. Hey, lover.
- Hey.

12:54.807 --> 12:56.808
What on earth are you doing up?

12:56.809 --> 12:59.878
- I didn't sleep great.
- Hangover?

12:59.879 --> 13:02.080
- <font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font> Yeah.
- <i><font color="#808080">(BABY FUSSING)</font></i>

13:02.081 --> 13:04.883
How are you?

13:04.884 --> 13:08.186
Well, apparently they wake-up every
two hours and they demand food.

13:08.187 --> 13:11.556
- Who knew?
- Can I help?

13:11.557 --> 13:16.394
Yes, you could fix the garage
doors. They're driving me crazy.

13:16.395 --> 13:17.995
<i>Just gonna grab some diapers.</i>

13:19.531 --> 13:22.367
<font color="#804040">WOMAN ON TV</font>: <i>...blamed a ride
home when she got into...</i>

13:22.368 --> 13:24.369
<font color="#804040">MAN</font>: <i>...in the third
period, they mounted...</i>

13:24.370 --> 13:27.005
<font color="#804040">MAN #2</font>: <i>...remind everybody that
no matter what the weather,</i>

13:27.006 --> 13:29.808
the winter festival
is happening...

13:29.809 --> 13:31.376
<font color="#804040">WOMAN</font>: <i>just be careful out
there, folks. The weather is...</i>

13:31.377 --> 13:32.911
- <font color="#804040">WIFE</font>: <i>Mitch.</i>
- Uh-huh.

13:32.912 --> 13:35.345
<font color="#804040">WIFE</font>: <i>Something you
wanna tell me?</i>

13:36.181 --> 13:38.016
What?

13:38.017 --> 13:39.983
About last night?

13:41.019 --> 13:42.187
<i><font color="#808080">(TV CLICKS OFF)</font>
</i>

13:42.188 --> 13:45.522
- What?
- <i>And the car?</i>

13:49.260 --> 13:51.295
Rach...

13:53.131 --> 13:54.599
uh...

13:54.600 --> 13:56.234
<i>And why it's parked
in the garage?</i>

13:56.235 --> 13:57.968
Did you drive home?

14:01.906 --> 14:03.541
Yeah.

14:03.542 --> 14:06.311
- <i>You promised to take a cab.</i>
- I know.

14:06.312 --> 14:08.379
No, I mean... What, are you crazy?
'Cause if you get a D.U.I.,

14:08.380 --> 14:09.948
then you can kiss the
D.A.'s office goodbye.

14:09.949 --> 14:11.549
I know. I know, I'm sorry.

14:11.550 --> 14:13.585
I shouldn't have. I
won't do it again.

14:13.586 --> 14:15.587
Mitch, I am serious.
You're a father now, okay?

14:15.588 --> 14:17.622
You can't afford
to take chances.

14:17.623 --> 14:20.558
I know. I'm sorry.

14:20.559 --> 14:22.927
I'm sorry.

14:22.928 --> 14:25.462
See? Look, even Ella agrees.

14:26.297 --> 14:27.464
Ella?

14:28.399 --> 14:30.001
Are you sure?

14:30.002 --> 14:32.669
Mm-hmm. Don't change the topic.

14:34.105 --> 14:36.641
I don't know what I'd
do if I lost you guys.

14:36.642 --> 14:39.611
Mmm. Here, let me take her.
You go to bed.

14:39.612 --> 14:42.447
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font>
Go get some rest.

14:42.448 --> 14:44.315
- There you go. Thanks.
- <i><font color="#808080">(TRUCK APPROACHES)</font></i>

14:44.316 --> 14:47.285
Just an hour.

14:47.286 --> 14:49.621
<font color="#808080">(ELLA AND MITCH SIGH)</font>

14:49.622 --> 14:51.989
- <i><font color="#808080">(BRAKES SQUEAK)</font></i>
- Shh shh shh.

14:59.664 --> 15:02.466
<font color="#808080">(WHIRRING)</font>

15:13.111 --> 15:15.012
<i><font color="#808080">(TRASH CAN THUMPS)</font>
</i>

15:24.455 --> 15:26.623
<i><font color="#808080">(KEYS JINGLING)</font>
</i>

15:41.940 --> 15:44.107
<i><font color="#808080">(GARAGE DOOR RATTLING, SQUEAKING OPEN)</font>
</i>

15:46.544 --> 15:48.078
<i><font color="#808080">(CAR ALARM CHIRPS)</font>
</i>

16:03.027 --> 16:05.062
- <font color="#808080">(CLEARS THROAT)</font> Hey.
- You okay?

16:06.030 --> 16:08.032
Yeah. Could you call around

16:08.033 --> 16:09.667
the local hospitals and clinics?

16:09.668 --> 16:11.536
I'm trying to track down a
young man who was involved

16:11.537 --> 16:13.972
in a hit-and-run accident
last night around midnight.

16:13.973 --> 16:17.240
- What case is it connected to?
- Just let me know what you find.

16:21.579 --> 16:23.081
<font color="#808080">(PLASTIC CUP RUSTLES)</font>

16:23.082 --> 16:24.848
<font color="#808080">(GROANS)</font>

16:29.220 --> 16:31.756
<i><font color="#808080">(RADIO CHATTER)</font>
</i>

16:31.757 --> 16:34.058
- <font color="#804040">MAN</font>: Yeah.
- <font color="#804040">WOMAN</font>: Over there.

16:34.059 --> 16:35.692
<font color="#804040">MAN</font>: Thanks.

16:41.733 --> 16:43.634
- Morning, officers.
- Good morning.

16:43.635 --> 16:46.303
- Good. This way.
- Thanks.

16:54.045 --> 16:56.247
<font color="#804040">REPORTER</font>: <i>I'm down here in
front of the police department</i>

16:56.248 --> 16:59.150
with the story of the tragic
death of this local young man.

16:59.151 --> 17:02.653
What started out as a routine
traffic stop last night

17:02.654 --> 17:05.455
has turned into a gruesome
murder investigation

17:05.457 --> 17:07.425
<i>when police officers
stopped this van</i>

17:07.425 --> 17:09.426
<i>parked behind me in
the police impound</i>

17:09.428 --> 17:11.596
for nothing more than a
burnt-out taillight.

17:11.597 --> 17:14.098
When they saw blood dripping
from the rear door,

17:14.098 --> 17:15.767
they demanded the
driver open the van

17:15.768 --> 17:19.103
and it was then they discovered
the body of Cecil Ackerman,

17:19.104 --> 17:21.806
<i>a 24-year-old parolee
from Naperville.</i>

17:21.807 --> 17:24.041
Please don't.

17:24.042 --> 17:25.810
<i>The driver claims
he found Ackerman</i>

17:25.810 --> 17:28.479
dying in the road from
an apparent hit-and-run

17:28.480 --> 17:30.748
and was merely trying to
get him to the hospital.

17:30.749 --> 17:33.416
<i>This is Jeff Franklin,
reporting live from the scene.</i>

17:47.598 --> 17:48.800
Hey, counselor.

17:48.801 --> 17:51.168
- <i><font color="#808080">(BUZZES)</font></i>
- Thanks.

17:54.172 --> 17:56.339
<font color="#808080">(CHATTERING)</font>

18:03.614 --> 18:05.182
<font color="#804040">WOMAN</font>: Yeah?

18:06.517 --> 18:08.352
- Detective Kanon?
- Yeah.

18:08.353 --> 18:10.388
How many "T"s in "committed"?

18:10.389 --> 18:13.823
- Two.
- Fucking paperwork.

18:14.859 --> 18:16.794
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font>
You got here fast.

18:16.795 --> 18:19.163
Yeah.

18:19.164 --> 18:20.631
You said you were interested
in the Ackerman murder?

18:20.632 --> 18:22.166
- Yes, I am.
- <i><font color="#808080">(PAPER RUSTLES)</font></i>

18:22.167 --> 18:24.701
D.A. assigned just you?

18:26.170 --> 18:28.305
Well, it's just a
provisional inquiry.

18:31.642 --> 18:33.310
<i>Walk with me.</i>

18:36.747 --> 18:39.150
<i>Suspect's name is
Clinton Davis.</i>

18:39.151 --> 18:41.853
<i>55; Car mechanic;</i>

18:41.854 --> 18:45.223
<i>couple of assault charges,
nothing he did time for;</i>

18:45.224 --> 18:47.658
no relatives; Wife and
daughter were murdered

18:47.659 --> 18:49.859
in a home invasion
a few years back.

18:50.695 --> 18:52.563
Priest was in here already,

18:52.564 --> 18:54.765
saying what a good guy he is,
how he'd never hurt a fly,

18:54.766 --> 18:55.900
- et cetera.
- They said on the news

18:55.901 --> 18:58.269
that he found Cecil
Ackerman in the road.

18:58.270 --> 19:00.371
Yeah, we've been there.

19:00.372 --> 19:02.773
No broken car parts, no
blood that we could see.

19:02.774 --> 19:05.375
Yeah, but the snow
thawed overnight, so...

19:07.345 --> 19:10.248
we've got Ackerman's blood and
hair all over Davis' clothes.

19:10.249 --> 19:13.351
We've got the bloody tools and the
plastic sheets in the back of his van.

19:13.352 --> 19:14.886
We've got enough to charge him.

19:14.887 --> 19:17.887
You guys need to decide if
it's enough to convict.

19:19.724 --> 19:22.293
- He looks terrified.
- He should be.

19:22.294 --> 19:25.862
He's staring down 20 to
life for this one alone.

19:27.365 --> 19:29.400
This one?

19:29.401 --> 19:30.902
I ran some keywords
through the database.

19:30.903 --> 19:33.436
It flagged a string of
unsolved homicides.

19:34.572 --> 19:36.640
You think this guy's
a serial killer?

19:38.242 --> 19:40.277
You don't even know that
he killed this guy.

19:41.913 --> 19:44.481
Tell your boss we'll send
him everything we got.

19:45.583 --> 19:47.284
<i><font color="#808080">(DOOR OPENS)</font>
</i>

19:48.419 --> 19:49.919
<i><font color="#808080">(DOOR CLOSES)</font>
</i>

20:01.265 --> 20:03.333
- <i><font color="#808080">(KNOCKS)</font></i>
- <i><font color="#808080">(DOOR OPENS)</font></i>

20:04.769 --> 20:08.605
- Mitch.
- I have a request, Sir.

20:10.608 --> 20:12.977
Thanks. Hey.

20:12.978 --> 20:15.313
Mitch Brockden, D.A.'s office.

20:15.314 --> 20:16.914
My associate Stuart Wilson.

20:16.915 --> 20:19.283
Terry Roberts, public
defender's office.

20:19.284 --> 20:20.784
There you go.

20:23.921 --> 20:26.224
Mr. Davis, we're going to
ask you a few questions

20:26.225 --> 20:27.592
about the night of the 4th.

20:27.593 --> 20:29.994
If you can answer as
accurately as possible...

20:29.995 --> 20:32.862
You're gonna be my prosecutor?

20:33.798 --> 20:35.633
Uh, if this goes to trial,

20:35.634 --> 20:37.001
then yes, I am.

20:37.002 --> 20:40.004
I didn't do anything.
I'm innocent.

20:40.005 --> 20:41.973
Then you've got nothing
to worry about.

20:41.974 --> 20:44.609
Okay, Mr. Davis,

20:44.610 --> 20:46.978
let's start with you
telling us where you were

20:46.979 --> 20:49.981
earlier that evening.

20:49.982 --> 20:52.516
Left work, went to group,

20:52.517 --> 20:54.485
went for a drive.

20:54.486 --> 20:55.987
Group?

20:55.988 --> 20:59.890
Yeah, I help out at
some support groups.

20:59.891 --> 21:03.461
- And the drive?
- Just something I do.

21:03.462 --> 21:05.730
It's not against the law, right?

21:05.731 --> 21:09.032
I mean, don't you ever go out
and drive around at night?

21:12.870 --> 21:15.339
Due respect, I think
that's beside the point.

21:15.340 --> 21:17.642
I don't like to spend
too much time at home.

21:17.643 --> 21:19.477
It brings back memories...

21:19.478 --> 21:22.746
My wife and child.

21:25.049 --> 21:27.285
Uh, yes.

21:27.286 --> 21:29.353
I heard what happened
to your family.

21:29.354 --> 21:31.755
I'm... I'm sorry.

21:33.057 --> 21:35.526
Emanuel fryer. Gunned
down the next night

21:35.527 --> 21:37.660
attacking someone else's family.

21:39.497 --> 21:41.332
<font color="#804040">MAN</font>: <i>What do we know
about the victim?</i>

21:41.333 --> 21:44.602
<font color="#804040">STUART</font>: Cecil Ackerman...
registered sex offender;

21:44.603 --> 21:47.071
two counts of child sex
abuse; Did two years inside;

21:47.072 --> 21:49.073
was only out on
parole three months.

21:49.074 --> 21:51.709
So a real loss to society.

21:51.710 --> 21:54.445
So far there's no connection
between him and Davis.

21:54.446 --> 21:57.048
- What about the murder weapon?
- Weapons.

21:57.049 --> 21:59.617
The coroner couldn't be exact,

21:59.618 --> 22:01.552
but he suggested these
wounds could be consistent

22:01.553 --> 22:03.054
with the type of tools
and machine parts

22:03.055 --> 22:05.089
found in the back of Davis' van.

22:05.090 --> 22:07.058
- Could be?
- Well, they also found

22:07.059 --> 22:09.327
significant amounts of oil
and grit in the wounds,

22:09.328 --> 22:11.462
which corroborates Davis'
hit-and-run story.

22:11.463 --> 22:13.364
True, but the Vic's D.N.A.
And blood were

22:13.365 --> 22:15.366
all over Davis' clothes,
inside his van.

22:15.367 --> 22:17.702
Which could've got there when he
lifted Ackerman into his van.

22:17.703 --> 22:19.937
Yeah, or when he murdered him.
Davis has two counts

22:19.938 --> 22:21.739
- of aggravated assault.
- At a time when his family

22:21.740 --> 22:23.708
had just been murdered
in a home invasion.

22:23.709 --> 22:26.944
He hasn't had so much as
a parking ticket since.

22:26.945 --> 22:28.779
What's bothering you, Mitch?

22:28.780 --> 22:30.614
I don't see motive.

22:30.615 --> 22:32.715
- <i><font color="#808080">(KNOCKS)</font></i>
- <i><font color="#808080">(DOOR OPENS)</font></i>

22:34.085 --> 22:36.420
Just got this audio file.

22:36.421 --> 22:39.090
<font color="#808080">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>
Here's the transcript.

22:39.091 --> 22:41.659
<i>It was a 911 call. Somebody
called in an accident</i>

22:41.660 --> 22:43.661
<i>20 minutes before
Davis was picked up.</i>

22:43.662 --> 22:46.430
<i>By the time the ambulance
arrived at the location,</i>

22:46.431 --> 22:48.599
<i>there was no one there.</i>

22:48.600 --> 22:50.600
<font color="#804040">MAN</font>: <i>Okay, thank you.</i>

22:52.570 --> 22:55.139
Is there any way we
can find the caller?

22:55.140 --> 22:58.174
- No, he used a payphone.
- How do you know that?

22:59.844 --> 23:03.447
If he used his cell, it would
have his name, phone records.

23:03.448 --> 23:06.450
<font color="#804040">MAN</font>: <i>Okay, 911 call's
potentially damaging,</i>

23:06.451 --> 23:08.386
<i>but it's not conclusive.</i>

23:08.387 --> 23:10.154
<i>And if we can't
find the caller,</i>

23:10.155 --> 23:12.490
<i>defense probably can't either.</i>

23:12.491 --> 23:14.759
<i>Could be anyone in Chicago.</i>

23:14.760 --> 23:17.928
Mitch, where were
you that evening?

23:17.929 --> 23:18.670
<i><font color="#808080">(LAUGHS)</font>
</i>

23:18.671 --> 23:21.399
- No, Mitch couldn't
string a sentence together

23:21.400 --> 23:23.033
- that night, right, Mitch?
- <font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

23:23.034 --> 23:25.669
- Yeah, thanks, Stu.
- <i>If it was a hit-and-run,</i>

23:25.670 --> 23:27.938
all it takes is for
the guy who hit him

23:27.939 --> 23:30.674
<i>to come forward and confess,
and we're dead in the water.</i>

23:30.675 --> 23:34.512
<font color="#804040">STUART</font>: <i>What's the likelihood
of anybody doing that, huh?</i>

23:34.513 --> 23:38.549
<font color="#804040">BOTTOM LINE</font>: Do we have
enough for a conviction?

23:38.550 --> 23:41.519
Davis was found with a
dead man in his van.

23:41.520 --> 23:43.521
We have a ton of
physical evidence.

23:43.522 --> 23:45.890
No alibi, a documented
history of violence

23:45.891 --> 23:47.491
and his public defender's
still in diapers.

23:47.492 --> 23:49.692
Mitch will eat him
for breakfast.

23:56.167 --> 23:59.002
Charge him, murder one.

24:06.977 --> 24:09.245
<font color="#804040">MITCH</font>: You examined
the body, doctor.

24:10.514 --> 24:13.517
In your professional... opinion,

24:13.518 --> 24:16.020
what was the 'cause of death?

24:16.021 --> 24:17.988
Blunt force trauma to the skull.

24:17.989 --> 24:19.924
And what caused that trauma?

24:19.925 --> 24:22.226
The back of the skull
was badly crushed,

24:22.227 --> 24:25.729
so it's hard to narrow
it down to any one item,

24:25.730 --> 24:27.865
but some of the marks
seemed consistent

24:27.866 --> 24:30.568
with a hammer found
in the suspect's van.

24:30.569 --> 24:34.038
And the interior was covered
in grease and motor oil,

24:34.039 --> 24:37.942
so any type of violent
struggle in that environment

24:37.943 --> 24:42.046
could've also caused those wounds
and left that trace evidence.

24:42.047 --> 24:44.748
You said, "seemed consistent."

24:44.749 --> 24:47.016
That's correct.

24:48.752 --> 24:51.755
Your report talks of abrasions

24:51.756 --> 24:56.192
and impact wounds with grease
and motor oil in them.

24:57.528 --> 25:00.096
Now the defense I'm sure
is gonna argue that...

25:00.965 --> 25:02.933
<i>those wounds indicate</i>

25:02.934 --> 25:05.536
<i>that a car ran over
Cecil Ackerman</i>

25:05.537 --> 25:07.972
as per the defendant's testimony

25:07.973 --> 25:10.607
and that the rest is just...

25:11.775 --> 25:14.744
a misinterpretation
of the evidence.

25:16.146 --> 25:18.648
No more questions, your honor.

25:25.589 --> 25:27.124
<font color="#804040">OPERATOR</font>: <i>911, what's
your emergency?</i>

25:27.125 --> 25:29.260
<i><font color="#808080">(MITCH PANTING)</font>
I need an ambulance.</i>

25:29.261 --> 25:32.296
- <i>A guy's been hit by a car.</i>
- <i>What's the location, Sir?</i>

25:32.297 --> 25:34.265
<i>Uh, Keeler. Keeler and 26th.</i>

25:34.266 --> 25:36.000
<font color="#804040">OPERATOR</font>: <i>What's
your name, Sir?</i>

25:36.001 --> 25:37.735
<font color="#804040">MITCH</font>: <i>Please just hurry.</i>

25:37.736 --> 25:40.069
- <i>Hurry, he's hurt real bad.</i>
- OPERATOR: <i>Sir.</i>

25:41.605 --> 25:44.340
It's your witness, Mr. Brockden.

25:50.080 --> 25:55.252
Doctor, the jury will be unfamiliar
with your field of expertise,

25:55.253 --> 25:58.322
so I'll ask quite a
simple question.

25:58.323 --> 26:01.759
Just how accurate is
forensic linguistics?

26:01.760 --> 26:04.295
- Extremely.
- But it's not perfect?

26:04.296 --> 26:06.697
Perfection doesn't
happen in science.

26:06.698 --> 26:10.801
Okay. On a sliding scale
of one to 10 then...

26:10.802 --> 26:13.637
you may want to
object, counselor.

26:13.638 --> 26:15.873
<i>The witness' field is
not on trial here.</i>

26:15.874 --> 26:17.494
I'll withdraw the
question, your honor.

26:19.310 --> 26:21.011
<i>You stated earlier
that you believe</i>

26:21.012 --> 26:23.681
the caller to be genuine?

26:23.682 --> 26:26.884
By this I assume you mean

26:26.885 --> 26:28.886
he was reporting
a real accident.

26:28.887 --> 26:30.119
Correct.

26:31.188 --> 26:33.324
And you can tell this just by...

26:33.325 --> 26:34.692
hearing his voice?

26:34.693 --> 26:38.195
It's more complicated
than that, but yes.

26:38.196 --> 26:41.230
What else can you tell
us about the caller?

26:42.666 --> 26:44.001
Hard to be certain

26:44.002 --> 26:45.369
from the quality of the tape.

26:45.370 --> 26:49.006
Sounded like a white male...
possibly in his 30s...

26:49.007 --> 26:50.841
from the South of Chicago,

26:50.842 --> 26:52.810
but he's tried hard
to soften the accent,

26:52.811 --> 26:54.678
not unlike yourself, counselor.

26:54.679 --> 26:56.146
Now you're from
where, Riverdale?

26:56.147 --> 26:58.014
When you say it's hard
to tell for certain...

26:59.617 --> 27:00.918
that the tape is unclear,

27:00.919 --> 27:03.354
that it <i>seems</i> to
be a white male...

27:03.355 --> 27:05.923
<font color="#804040">WOMAN</font>: <i>The
underlying ethnicity</i>

27:05.924 --> 27:08.825
is hard to fully hide
from trained ears.

27:10.361 --> 27:13.364
<i><font color="#808080">(WOMEN CHATTERING)</font>
</i>

27:13.365 --> 27:16.700
- Yes, it's a good recording.
- Uh-huh.

27:16.701 --> 27:19.269
<i><font color="#808080">(CHATTER CONTINUES)</font>
</i>

27:19.270 --> 27:21.738
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you too.

27:26.710 --> 27:29.346
- Hey.
- Staff meeting starts in five.

27:29.347 --> 27:32.082
Someone named Jimmy called,
wouldn't leave a last name.

27:32.083 --> 27:34.718
Said to tell you he's out
and wants to see you.

27:34.719 --> 27:36.920
Left a contact number. Do you want
me to get him on the phone for you?

27:36.921 --> 27:38.855
No no no, thank you.

27:41.859 --> 27:44.895
<font color="#808080">(INHALES)</font>
Smell that?

27:44.896 --> 27:47.364
That's the smell of freedom.

27:47.365 --> 27:49.031
<font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

27:53.137 --> 27:55.739
Hey, so I called your
house the other day,

27:55.740 --> 27:57.440
you know, looking for ya.

27:59.710 --> 28:01.277
Your wife...

28:02.413 --> 28:04.814
she doesn't know who
I am, does she?

28:05.983 --> 28:07.785
You've been gone a
long time, Jimmy.

28:07.786 --> 28:09.753
How do you not tell her about
your own fucking brother?

28:09.754 --> 28:10.787
Step-brother.

28:12.122 --> 28:14.223
And let's face it,
legally not even that.

28:16.393 --> 28:19.829
- You wanna play like that.
- Don't be fucking cute with me, Jimmy.

28:20.431 --> 28:22.766
I was working at that warehouse

28:22.767 --> 28:25.501
to pay my way through law
school when you fucking hit it!

28:26.804 --> 28:29.973
I could've been done as a
fucking accessory. Huh?

28:29.974 --> 28:32.776
- Bye-bye, career.
- Yeah, I know. I was fucking stupid.

28:32.777 --> 28:34.244
<font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

28:34.245 --> 28:35.946
Fuck, Mitch.

28:35.947 --> 28:38.414
I mean, Jesus, I was doing
a lot of drugs back then.

28:39.450 --> 28:40.451
I was selfish.

28:40.452 --> 28:42.186
I've had a lot of fucking time

28:42.187 --> 28:44.488
to think about my life,
think about who I was.

28:44.489 --> 28:46.422
Okay?

28:47.458 --> 28:48.958
Now I let you down.

28:50.494 --> 28:52.261
But I will not let
you down again.

28:55.099 --> 28:56.465
Look...

28:58.102 --> 29:00.303
I met Rachel when
I was graduating.

29:01.772 --> 29:04.775
She processed my application
to the D.A.'s office.

29:04.776 --> 29:07.044
Seeing as my ma never
officially married your dad...

29:07.045 --> 29:09.111
yeah, you figured why
mention us, right?

29:10.314 --> 29:12.015
Jimmy, it was best for
me not to have ties

29:12.016 --> 29:13.983
- to a criminal past, you know?
- <font color="#808080">(SNORTS)</font>

29:15.219 --> 29:16.487
Once I'd lied on the forms,

29:16.488 --> 29:19.155
- I couldn't tell...
- Yeah, I get it.

29:20.023 --> 29:21.324
I understand.

29:23.961 --> 29:27.063
- God.
- I'm not that kid anymore.

29:29.533 --> 29:31.033
Riverdale, it's...

29:32.903 --> 29:35.004
It was another life.

29:36.340 --> 29:38.007
Well, lucky you.

29:39.543 --> 29:41.210
I only got the one.

29:43.814 --> 29:45.314
Hey.

29:47.851 --> 29:50.019
<i><font color="#808080">(KEYBOARD CLICKING)</font>
</i>

30:06.904 --> 30:09.071
<font color="#808080">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

30:11.508 --> 30:14.878
- <font color="#808080">(BEEPS)</font>
- Hello?

30:14.879 --> 30:17.246
<i>Hey, Mr. Brockden. It's Kanon.</i>

30:18.348 --> 30:19.916
Detective Kanon.

30:21.084 --> 30:22.386
What can I do for you?

30:22.387 --> 30:24.420
<i>Just checking in.</i>

30:25.422 --> 30:26.824
<i>We lost a point or two</i>

30:26.825 --> 30:28.524
<i>on that forensic linguist.</i>

30:29.560 --> 30:30.927
Yeah.

30:31.595 --> 30:33.564
Yeah, I know. It's, umm...

30:33.565 --> 30:38.235
it's almost impossible to
make Davis the caller, so...

30:38.236 --> 30:40.303
<i>Right.</i>

30:41.905 --> 30:43.574
It's kinda late, detective.

30:43.575 --> 30:45.542
Is there something you need?

30:45.543 --> 30:47.544
<i>No, just wanted to know</i>

30:47.545 --> 30:49.479
<i>that you're ready
for tomorrow.</i>

30:49.480 --> 30:51.147
<i><font color="#808080">(LINE CLICKS)</font>
</i>

30:53.383 --> 30:56.218
- What was that?
- <i>What?</i>

30:58.055 --> 30:59.990
You're recording this?

30:59.991 --> 31:02.092
<i>Why would I be recording this?</i>

31:02.093 --> 31:05.562
<i><font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font> They say
that cops are paranoid.</i>

31:05.563 --> 31:08.030
<i>See you in court.</i>

31:16.273 --> 31:18.307
<font color="#808080">(BREATHES DEEPLY)</font>

31:24.281 --> 31:26.649
<font color="#808080">(SIGHS)</font>

31:36.326 --> 31:39.028
She's asleep. Hey.

31:39.663 --> 31:40.631
Hey.

31:40.632 --> 31:42.466
<i><font color="#808080">(FRIDGE OPENS)</font>
</i>

31:42.467 --> 31:44.434
- You smell like milk.
- <font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

31:44.435 --> 31:46.536
- Ella was sick on me, again.
- <i><font color="#808080">(FRIDGE CLOSES)</font></i>

31:46.537 --> 31:48.504
- <i><font color="#808080">(GLASS CLATTERS)</font></i>
- Nice.

31:51.008 --> 31:53.644
<i>Mitch. Hey.</i>

31:53.645 --> 31:55.444
Look at me.

31:57.681 --> 31:59.215
Mitch.

32:01.985 --> 32:03.686
What is it?

32:05.522 --> 32:07.623
Is there something
you're not telling me?

32:09.226 --> 32:10.726
Yes.

32:12.496 --> 32:14.130
What? Can't you just...

32:15.999 --> 32:17.666
Tell me?

32:22.039 --> 32:23.672
I love you.

32:26.710 --> 32:28.177
<font color="#808080">(CHUCKLES)</font>

32:32.182 --> 32:34.484
<font color="#808080">(EXHALES DEEPLY)</font>

32:34.485 --> 32:36.085
I love you too.

32:37.587 --> 32:41.090
<font color="#808080">(BREATHES DEEPLY)</font>

32:43.060 --> 32:44.427
<font color="#804040">BAILIFF</font>: <i>All rise.</i>

32:51.335 --> 32:52.535
Be seated.

32:53.670 --> 32:55.739
Before session
begins, your honor,

32:55.740 --> 32:58.207
I would like to
approach the bench.

32:59.276 --> 33:02.279
I will not tolerate
tardiness, Mr. Roberts.

33:02.280 --> 33:04.715
I'm sorry, your honor,
but there has been

33:04.716 --> 33:07.116
an important development.

33:10.687 --> 33:13.090
Defense would like to
call a new witness.

33:13.091 --> 33:16.426
Objection, your honor. The
prosecution wasn't informed of this.

33:16.427 --> 33:19.529
<font color="#804040">TERRY</font>: <i>Defense was unaware of their
identity until late last night.</i>

33:19.530 --> 33:22.099
What is the relevance of
this witness, Mr. Roberts?

33:22.100 --> 33:23.767
He's the man who
made the 911 call.

33:23.768 --> 33:25.469
- <font color="#804040">PEOPLE</font>: <i>What? What?</i>
- Order!

33:25.470 --> 33:27.571
- <i><font color="#808080">(GAVEL BANGS)</font></i>
- JUDGE: <i>Order.</i>

33:27.572 --> 33:29.272
- Your honor...
- I'm inclined to allow it, Mr. Brockden.

33:29.273 --> 33:31.274
Yes, I understand that,
but if you could just...

33:31.275 --> 33:33.643
- <i>Mr. Brockden!</i>
- TERRY: <i>Dr. Brown's lab</i>

33:33.644 --> 33:37.547
ran a voice analysis overnight
and we got a viable match.

33:37.548 --> 33:40.083
How soon can defense
present this witness?

33:40.084 --> 33:42.019
Right away, your honor.
He's been in the courtroom

33:42.020 --> 33:43.787
- this entire trial.
- MITCH: <i>Your honor, please!</i>

33:43.788 --> 33:45.756
- Can I just please say some...
- <i><font color="#808080">(GAVEL BANGS)</font></i>

33:45.757 --> 33:47.758
Enough!

33:47.759 --> 33:49.658
Call your witness.

33:50.594 --> 33:52.761
The defense calls...

33:54.264 --> 33:56.099
- <i>Jimmy Logan to the stand.</i>
- MAN: <i>What?</i>

33:56.100 --> 33:58.267
<font color="#808080">(MURMURING)</font>

34:10.047 --> 34:11.581
<font color="#804040">REPORTER</font>: <i>In a surprise
twist of events,</i>

34:11.581 --> 34:13.083
<i>a witness came forward today</i>

34:13.083 --> 34:14.351
<i>and ended the
prosecution's case</i>

34:14.351 --> 34:16.253
<i>against Clinton Davis.</i>

34:16.254 --> 34:18.588
<i>The witness saw the
victim, Cecil Ackerman,</i>

34:18.589 --> 34:20.456
<i>mowed down by a
hit-and-run driver</i>

34:20.458 --> 34:24.061
<i>in a red S.U.V. And left
on the road to die.</i>

34:24.062 --> 34:25.829
He then called 911.

34:25.830 --> 34:27.496
<font color="#808080">(REPORTERS CHATTER)</font>

34:27.498 --> 34:28.799
<font color="#804040">TERRY</font>: It seems
that Clinton Davis

34:28.800 --> 34:31.301
was not the only good
samaritan in this trial.

34:31.302 --> 34:33.469
<font color="#808080">(PEOPLE CHATTERING)</font>

34:34.504 --> 34:35.771
Mr. Davis?

34:38.675 --> 34:40.708
I just wanted to wish
you all the best.

34:41.545 --> 34:42.813
Yeah, it's like you said...

34:42.813 --> 34:46.215
if I was innocent,
everything would work out.

34:46.817 --> 34:48.717
Yes, I did.

34:48.719 --> 34:50.518
So what happens now?

